{
  "texts": [
    "• Only internal.",
    "The LLM can answer the question directly, but external documents cannot provide the solution.",
    "• Both internal and external.",
    "The question can be addressed either directly by the LLM or through retrieved documents.For comparison, both standard RAG [2] and ReAct [39] are put to the test on sampled 100 questions from HotpotQA dataset.From Figure 2, Our study yields several insights: (1) When the model operates without any knowledge, it faces difficulty in generating accurate responses.",
    "(2) When the model is based only on either internal or external knowledge, there's a noticeable accuracy improvement."
  ]
}